Description: Unique identifier assigned to the protein by UniProt. E.g. A0A024R1R8
Official gene symbol associated with the protein. E.g. TMA7B
Full name of the protein as listed in UniProt. E.g. Translation machinery-associated protein 7B
Total number of amino acids in the protein sequence. e.g. '117'
Residues that form the active site of the protein and any associated notes about the site. E.g. ACT_SITE 69; /note=Proton acceptor; /evidence=ECO:0000250

Residues that form the binding site of the protein (and ligands at those sites). E.g. BINDING 10; /ligand=substrate; /evidence=ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:O95989; BINDING 18..20; /ligand=substrate; /evidence=ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:O95989

Alternative products or isoforms that the gene can produce. Begins with 'ALTERNATIVE PRODUCTS: ' even if there are no isoforms (would be blank after). E.g. ALTERNATIVE PRODUCTS:  Event=Alternative splicing; Named isoforms=2; Name=1; IsoId=A0A096LP49-1; Sequence=Displayed; Name=2; IsoId=A0A096LP49-2; Sequence=VSP_058066;
Any other proteins that the gene/protein product may interact with. E.g. Q96S66

The body tissues that the gene is specific to. Begins with 'TISSUE SPECIFICITY: ' E.g. TISSUE SPECIFICITY: Detected in plasma (at protein level) (PubMed:25738459, PubMed:32182209). Also expressed in skeletal muscle (at protein level) (PubMed:32182209). {ECO:0000269|PubMed:25738459, ECO:0000269|PubMed:32182209}.

Biological processes (e.g. x catabolic process or y metabolic process) the gene is involved in. E.g. regulation of endoplasmic reticulum unfolded protein response [GO:1900101]; response to unfolded protein [GO:0006986]

The molecular function or activity the gene product is involved in. E.g. endopolyphosphatase activity, etc. E.g. ATP binding [GO:0005524]; identical protein binding [GO:0042802]; threonine-tRNA ligase activity [GO:0004829]
Residues that form the transmembrane domain of the gene product. Begins with 'TRANSMEM'. E.g. TRANSMEM 104..124; /note=Helical; /evidence=ECO:0000255
Residues that form the intermembrane domain of the gene product. Begins with 'INTRAMEM'. E.g. INTRAMEM 173..220; /evidence=ECO:0000305|PubMed:29915090

Residues involved in glycosylation. Begins with 'CARBOHYD'. E.g. CARBOHYD 124; /note=N-linked (GlcNAc...) asparagine; /evidence=ECO:0000255; CARBOHYD 125; /note=N-linked (GlcNAc...) asparagine; /evidence=ECO:0000255

Residues that have evidence of being modified (and what the modification is). Begins with 'MOD_RES'. E.g. MOD_RES 111; /note=Phosphoserine; by PKG; /evidence=ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:P55088; MOD_RES 180; /note=Phosphoserine; by PKC; /evidence=ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:P47863

Residues that have evidence of post translational modifications (and what the modification is). Begins with 'PTM'. E.g. PTM: Phosphorylated by tyrosine kinases in response to T-cell antigen receptor activation. Phosphorylated in mitotic cells. {ECO:0000250|UniProtKB:P46462}.; PTM: ISGylated. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:16139798}.
Residues/region involved in protein/molecule signaling. Begins with 'SIGNAL'. E.g. SIGNAL 1..18; /evidence=ECO:0000255
Residues/region forming the propeptide. Begins with 'PROPEP'. E.g. PROPEP 21..169; /evidence=ECO:0000255; /id=PRO_0000003749
Residues involved in lipidation. Begins with 'LIPID'. E.g. LIPID 361; /note=S-palmitoyl cysteine; /evidence=ECO:0000269|PubMed:21627585
Residues that form disulfide bonds. Begins with 'DISULFID'. E.g. DISULFID 73..124; /evidence=ECO:0000255|PROSITE-ProRule:PRU00114
Describes a short conserved sequence motif of biological significance. Begins with 'MOTIF' E.g. MOTIF 26..28; /note=Cell attachment site; /evidence=ECO:0000255
Any families the protein is a part of. E.g. Sauvagine/corticotropin-releasing factor/urotensin I family

Residues/region involved in protein/molecule signaling. Begins with 'ZN_FING'. E.g. ZN_FING 22..74; /note=PHD-type 1; /evidence=ECO:0000255|PROSITE-ProRule:PRU00146; ZN_FING 79..112; /note=C2HC pre-PHD-type; /evidence=ECO:0000255|PROSITE-ProRule:PRU01146

Regions of compositional bias within the protein and the particular type of amino acids that are over-represented within those regions. Begins with 'COMPBIAS'. E.g. COMPBIAS 291..306; /note=Polar residues; /evidence=ECO:0000256|SAM:MobiDB-lite; COMPBIAS 339..451; /note=Polar residues; /evidence=ECO:0000256|SAM:MobiDB-lite

Any notes or descriptions about a proteins domains. Begins with 'DOMAIN'. E.g. DOMAIN: The intra-membrane loop at the C-terminus acts as a calcium pore, mediating calcium leak from the ER into the cytosol. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:22128171}.
Region of the sequence with repeats.Begins with 'REPEAT'. E.g. REPEAT 41..69; /note=ANK 1; REPEAT 73..102; /note=ANK 2; REPEAT 106..135; /note=ANK 3; REPEAT 138..166; /note=ANK 4

Residues/region involved that form coiled coil motifs. Begins with 'COILED'. E.g. COILED 146..185; /evidence=ECO:0000255; COILED 1408..1448; /evidence=ECO:0000255; COILED 1523..1667; /evidence=ECO:0000255
Residues/regionwhich form the transit peptide. Begins with 'TRANSIT'. E.g. TRANSIT 1..33; /note=Mitochondrion; /evidence=ECO:0000269|PubMed:12665801, ECO:0007744|PubMed:25944712

Residues that form cross links. Begins with 'CROSSLNK'. E.g. CROSSLNK 384; /note=Glycyl lysine isopeptide (Lys-Gly) (interchain with G-Cter in SUMO2); /evidence=ECO:0007744|PubMed:28112733; CROSSLNK 408; /note=Glycyl lysine isopeptide (Lys-Gly) (interchain with G-Cter in SUMO2); /evidence=ECO:0007744|PubMed:28112733

Method of gene induction. What causes the gene to be expressed. Begins with 'INDUCTION'. E.g. INDUCTION: Isoform 1 is induced by interferon alpha. Isoform 5 is constitutively expressed. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:10200312, ECO:0000269|PubMed:7565688}.
The protein pathways that the gene product is involved in. Begins with 'PATHWAY'. E.g. PATHWAY: Purine metabolism; AMP biosynthesis via salvage pathway; AMP from adenosine: step 1/1.

How the protein is regulated by other proteins/molecules. Begins with 'ACTIVITY REGULATION: '. E.g. ACTIVITY REGULATION: Activated upon interaction by mucunain, a cowhage (Mucuna pruriens) plant cysteine proteinase. {ECO:0000269|PubMed:18434511}.

Description of the gene product's catalytic activity, if any. Begins with 'CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: ' E.g. CATALYTIC ACTIVITY: Reaction=H2O(in) = H2O(out); Xref=Rhea:RHEA:29667, ChEBI:CHEBI:15377; Evidence={ECO:0000269|PubMed:18768791, ECO:0000269|PubMed:23867895, ECO:0000269|PubMed:8621489};
Residues/region involved in binding DNA. Begins with 'DNA_BIND '. E.g. DNA_BIND 259..321; /note=Homeobox; TALE-type; /evidence=ECO:0000255|PROSITE-ProRule:PRU00108
Enzyme commission number (if any). E.g. '2.7.11.13'
Cofactors or essential molecules required for protein activity. E.g. COFACTOR: Name=Zn(2+); Xref=ChEBI:CHEBI:29105; Evidence={ECO:0000305}; Note=Binds 1 zinc ion per subunit. {ECO:0000305};
Unique identifier for a genetic condition or gene in the Online Mendelian Inheritance in Man (OMIM) database. E.g. '600639'
Chromosome that the gene is found on. E.g. 'chr2'
Genomic start position of the gene. E.g.' 38561542'
Genomic end position of the gene. E.g. '153489615'
Entrez ID for the gene. E.g. '729230'
Ensembl database identifier for the gene. E.g. ENSG00000135914
Organelle or cellular compartment(s) that the gene product localizes to. E.g. Microtubules,Cytokinetic bridge,Cytosol
For mitochondria localizing genes, the sub mitochondrial compartment where the gene is found. E.g. Matrix
For mitochondria localizing genes, the mitochondrial pathways the gene/gene product is involved in. E.g. Metabolism > Lipid metabolism > Fatty acid oxidation

The protein class of the disease product. E.g. Enzymes, disease related genes, predicted membrane proteins, transporters, etc. E.g. 'Enzymes, Metabolic proteins, Plasma proteins, Predicted intracellular proteins'
Whether the gene has high or low tissue specificity. E.g. 'Low tissue specificity' or 'Tissue enhanced' or 'Group enhanced'
The cell type(s) that a gene is specific to (if any). E.g. Cardiomyocytes: 26.2;dendritic cells: 81.0;Ovarian stromal cells: 103.4
Antibody identifier(s). E.g. HPA048636
